QUESTION-The Collection in Java is a framework that provides an architecture to store and manipulate the group of objects.
Java Collections can achieve all the operations that you perform on a data such as searching, sorting, insertion, manipulation, and deletion. 
Java Collection means a single unit of objects.
Sample Input:
18
10
5

SOLUTION-package collections;
import java.util.*;
import java.util.ArrayList;

public class collection_prog1 {

	public static void main(String[] args) {
		ArrayList<Integer> list= new ArrayList<Integer>();
		list.add(18);
		list.add(10);
		list.add(5);
		list.add(2);
		list.remove(3);// remove element of 3rd index
		Iterator itr= list.iterator();
		while(itr.hasNext()) {
			System.out.println(itr.next());
		}

	}

}
